<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A premium bayside suburb with a marina, a genuine village precinct, and a buyer profile that does not compromise.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Manly sits approximately seventeen kilometres east of the Brisbane CBD on Moreton Bay, occupying a position in Brisbane's eastern bayside corridor that places it among the more sought-after addresses at its price point. The Manly Boat Harbour and Cambridge Parade are the defining features of the suburb's identity: the harbour brings a marina atmosphere and sailing culture that you do not find in most Brisbane suburbs, and Cambridge Parade provides a well-established strip of cafes, restaurants and specialty retailers that serves as the social and commercial centre of the community. This is a suburb where the lifestyle has been established over decades rather than being built around recent development.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
